For those that need/want CalDAV support on Android, this app is an excellent way to get it, and an absolute bargain for the price. Setup is fairly straightforward, requiring basic details for your CalDAV server and a login/password if you need one. Once connected, your server will appear as an account just like any other service, and integrates directly with your standard Android Calendar app, giving you immediate, hassle-free access to your CalDAV calendar(s). Default settings are appropriate for most users, and there are a wealth of options for customising how often often, and how far ahead, CalDAV sync will download short term and long term calendar events, as well as options for dealing with any minor compatibility issues that may be encountered with some CalDAV servers. Overall a very robust, easy to use and painless CalDAV implementation, adding a sorely missing feature of Android that I can't believe is still absent!

Keeps telling me i cant have two caldavs under same username/email. Now I'm stuck downloading a second call Dev app just to get my second calendar to work.
replyContent: This limitation is set by Google. On Android, Account names have to be unique for each app and Android uses email addresses as account names. The solution: Enter a different email address in the last step of the setup. It doesn't even have to be a valid email address, eg. just "account2". /sa

content: I had a problem with syncing for a while. Turned out the problem was in the system settings. For some of you who encounter the same problem, try to check these settings: 1. Permissions to start in the background (self explanatory) Now I can sync seamlessy with Fastmail, iCloud & Gmail

It's an Android bug:
1. Check auto sync setting at [Android settings - Accounts & Sync].
2. Set the sync interval to a different value and close the app. Then reset it to the previous value.
2. Android 7 still has the doze mode bug: Add an exception for our apps at [Android settings - Battery - Battery optimization].

Or a mail to support@dmfs.org

Sync with my private cloud calendar perfectly.

So far I've been using this on my nexus 7 as well as Galaxy SII and it is a perfect app, enough features but not too many to make it complicated. Plus it works perfectly getting calendar data to and from my iCloud account
Installed this to sync with my iPhone, works faultlessly. Does exactly what it says it will. Haven't tried syncing an event back to the iPhone yet though
This app had problems with my calendar provider initially but the developer worked quickly to provide a work around. The app works flawlessly and I can't live without it.
Works great with my office's Oracle Convergence calendar
Works perfectly syncing with my OwnCloud calendar.
Brilliant piece of software. I am using it to sync calDAV calendars with my Synology DiskStation.
I've used this for months now and it works great! Ignore the nonsense comments about losing data on reboots. It works perfectly across reboots.
Informed developer of the bugs in JB (as commented by virus) and he came up with solutions in less than 5 days. What's more can I say...

This app has to be running all the time in background, which means when you stop the app OR restart the phone, all entries are lost and you have to setup the account all over again. Beware, the data is not persistent. Useless !
replyContent:
Please install the workaround app mentioned in the app description. The problem is caused by a bug in Android.
Also, when you uninstall the app then Android automatically removes all synced data. There is nothing the app can do about it.

content: Using it with owncloud 4.0.4
Works great own cloud calendar
Need a way to rename calenders locally
Connects to my Zimbra install w/o a hitch.
Works like a charm, hardly notice it's there, which is a good thing. It simply just works.
this is a fantastic application, and the developers provide excellent support.
Great!
Really works good with my server
Tested with Meeting Maker server CalDAV plugin
Just perfect. Even syncs with the non-standards-compliant Radicale caldav-server with self-signed certificate. Thanks.
Fully functional. Exception support for recurring events is great!

Have been using it for > 2 months now.  Work perfect with Zimbra.  I sync with calendar only for now.  Have problem with some interim version, but the current one is perfect.  Have tried another one specifically for Zimbra, but this one just works.
This gets better and better. The developer really helps fast if you email them too.
Really works well, providing a good background sync
Does exactly what it says on the tin
Works great with icloud

It works well on HTC phone with egroupware server. It was easy to setup connection to server but after connecting there were some parameters that needed more documentation like the difference between auto sync settings and long-term sync settings. Overall paid version works better than free version since it allows for 2-way syncing.
works like a charm!

I did not set SSL on the initial setup, and couldn't find a way to re-configure once installed. The dev was very responsive and helpful in helping me (had to remove and re-add connection). Works great on Evo 4G.
A nice, handy app...
It allows me to sync Thunderbird calendar with android via owncloud running on my desktop. I really like it!

I've been using this sysc, along with the carddav one. Both seem to work pretty well - I have no app complaints at all. 2-way syncing is great even if it is beta. Plays nicely with davical, testing owncloud didn't seem to work, (that could be me or owncloud that's a fault there). Developer provides configuration hint pages  for various different caldav servers.   Having had contact with the developer who has explained his position I'm retracting my previous statements regarding the open sourcing of the code. I look forward to the day this happens.
Tried a few apps to sync with caldav servers before.  This has been the most reliable and seamless.
Works great, no problems at all.
Works perfectly in HTC Her ans Galaxy S2

Tried several times now to no avail. Keep getting the "network error occurred..." message. Strange that my colleagues can get it working (on different phones in different places)! Uninstalling for now. Will try again in the future.
replyContent: Have you tried a recent version? Do you still get the same error?

content: Works really week with oracle beehive. Great responsiveness from the developer. Thanks
I got this app to connect my Android devices to my wife's iCloud account,  and it works great!
Perfect app. Even better support :)
Developer helped me solve it, despite it was egw problem, not caldav one.
Does exactly what it claims.   Zimbra, Moto Photon
As soon as I can sync attendees for existing appointments and create appointments with invites this will be a five star solution!
Works with Egroupware and was simple to setup..
I keep getting oops errors fix that & it will be 5 stars!!
Have used the CalDAV sync both way sync for 3 weeks now. Never a problem. Well worth the $.
Syncs with my office calendar (beehive). Keep up the good work.
Great app.  I have no real issues at this point.  It would be nice if you somehow associate it with .ics files so if someone emails you one it can be opened and then added to your calendar directly.
Easy to setup and configure.  Would like to see it sync with tasks like astrid in the future
Installed on my Xoom with ICS, it was able to synch my calendar perfectly.
Saves me so much hassle connecting to my group calendar. Very nice and helpful dev!

For 2 years now, my google calendar would not sync with my university's zimbra/yahoo cal - because of a robots.txt issues ( all over the forums as an issue). But this app fixed it instantly. Man I wish other huge problems ( and hours of trying) got fixed for $3.

This even seems to support automatically discovering my whole set of calendars on my Darwin calendar server account instead on needing to manually add each of them. Definately didn't expect that. *thumbs up*
Have been using this for ages and ages and it works perfectly. HTC Magic (aka Sapphire) & daviCal.
Marten provides great support.  Works well with native droid calendar.
Works very well

Syncs my yahoo calendar perfectly. It would be good to be able to schedule a background sync (ie every 6 hours or so) - my phone doesn't have a data plan so I'm not sure when it syncs as I go between wifi hotspots.

If you have multiple calendars on a zimbra server, then use this rather than Exchange ActiveSync -- this allows you to sync all of your zimbra calendars with the default Android calendar app. Works seamlessly.
I use it with SOGo for about half a year now and never had any problem.
Glad I waited a little and didn't rate it then. Now it's a five star app!
Works great on ics 4.0.
Great app.  Fast response time from developer.  Worth every penny
Awesome app.  I too was looking for a way to sync my calandar with iCloud.  Set up CalDav and hey presto, two way syncing worked a charm.
Works well with the family DaviCal server.
Works perfectly with my OS X iCal Server.
Works just fine with my own CalDAV server.  Easier than my wife's iPhone, actually.
This is the only product I've found that can work with Go Daddy calendars consistently via CalDAV.  It's much quicker than some of the other options too.  Great job - thanks!
Works great with my D3 and Zimbra OSS.
App works great! Thanks for answering all my questions so quickly!
Works brilliant with cloud
With zimbra and native HTC desire cal app

Switching over from iOS to Droid.  This was the only viable and integrated CalDAV application i found.  Too bad native CalDAV should be provided by the OS.  Why it isn't there is beyond me.  Anyway CalDAV-Sync saved the day.  But unfortunately unlike the CalDAV implemention on iOS this is not complete.  I cannot see and hence Accept/Decline calendar Invites.  For me it is a vital functionality.  I guess beggers can't be choosers.  Anyway I would have given it 5/5 if invites were working.
Synced my Tasks and my Calendar with little trouble. It's about time we could sync CalDAV to our android calendars.  Thanks!

Since switching to Android I've been frustrated by the lack of native CalDav support.  This app is the next best thing.  The way it integrates as a sync adaptor, my CalDav calendars show up in the native calendar app as well as a custom widget I use.  I can finally view and edit my work calendar on my phone.  I'm very pleased.

Purchased this app and tried to synch my Yahoo Calendar with my android phone: tried for hours.  Searched the internet for help support, tried everything.  Absolutely nothing worked.  Buyer be ware, this is not as easy as it looks. I have yet to make this work.
Works very well!
Worked fine for zimbra. When I bought my new phone (mytouch 4g slide) running gingerbread, the accect any ssl button was gone. This worked great
Works perfectly together with my ubuntu DAViCal-Server (apache2). My external brain is now better than my internal :-)
Works better than I expected!
Works great with our SOGo and Kerio systems. VERY stable for beta. Would love unified config UI with CardDav-Sync.
Works very well with Bedework's personal caldav server - two way sync with multiple calendars works nicely.  I haven't tried advanced features yet, but for basic CalDAV, this is very good.
Purchased the app because it claims to work with Yahoo. It took my account information and went through a sync cycle. But none of my events loaded

I needed this to sync with an older version of Zimbra, which it does perfectly. Setup was super easy--it figured out most of it on it's own. Now that it is configured, it just runs with no interaction required from me. Plus it integrates with every calendar widget I've tried with no problems. Even though it isn't officially supported for production use yet, Bi-directional sync Works flawlessly too (so far). Great app.
Awesome. Very reliable. Superb job.
Very good. Still some glitches but it's a beta after all. Keep up the good work!

My entire life is on Yahoo! Calender and this app makes the syncing of my phone's calender to my Yahoo! account seemless. I've done a bunch of tests of entering and deleting entries on the phone and on Yahoo!'s site and the syncing has been perfect.
Works perfectly with my Zimbra server!
I would have given five stars except it was really confusing for a non techie!
It's the only caldav app I can find that works. For me, two way sync works perfectly as well. In my case the server is a Zimbra server.

If you want CalDav to work on your device IN your native beautiful android calendar then you gotta get this. I was about to return my Galaxy Tab when I was unable to access a specific CalDav server. The dev worked with me to help resolve the issue and now it works beautifully. I recommend this dev for any project and you should buy his apps. I'm going to find out how to send him a six pack or something!
Great job! Works perfectly with Oracle Beehive
Works wonderfully. I have been using this for a few months now.
I've been using this with DaviCal for several days now and, so far, it's worked perfectly (including bidirectional synchronization).

What a great little application - simply works with the CalDav as designed. I have messed with configurations for days, wasted countless personal hours - on to productivity. Precisely what Marketplace development is all about - thanks Guys

Installed on my GS2 it two way syncs my calendars to my own DAViCal server which then syncs my Thunderbird calendars with no problems. For an alpha release this works remarkably well. I also use the CardDAV Sync and Contact Editor++ to complete my PIM syncing requirements.
Works great with yahoo.
So far it has worked very well with our OSS Zimbra. Plugs an otherwise gaping hole in Android. Simple to use and reliable. Many thanks for the work!
Syncs Yahoo calendar to my Samsumg Galaxy S2 perfectly.
Excellent! Using Zimbra 7.1.1.
Works **much** bettet than anDal. Using oracle beehive. Is there an option for read only?
Zero customer support.
Works well with Oracle Beehive. I initially had an issue with some recurring events, Marten fixed it almost immediately.

I bought this as I was looking for a way to sync my MobileMe (soon to be iCloud) calendars to my new phone. I set it up in a few minutes using the settings from iCal. I was amazed to see it work so flawlessly as I was not able to find any solutions to this problem elsewhere. Definitely recommended!!
First market purchase and worth every cent
Need to update my comment - it stopped working after an upgrade, but Marten immediately went to work and fixed it. It works well and GREAT service!
I was using a free ical sync application before this one and it suddenly stopped working after updating to gingerbread. This worked like a charm.
Works great, does the job perfectly. Recent updates are constant improvement and developer is very friendly! Recommended.
I'm using cardDAV too. This is seriously a nice piece of work. Works great for me with davical as server application.
Marten, didn't even know you got started on calDAV, but buying was a no-brainer based on how great your cardDAV is. This one is as good, thanks!

I have tried for months to get a working solution for Oracle's Calendar server and this worked within 5 of purchase. I should have bought it sooner. Two-way sync is still experimental and I can't wait for final release.
Works flawlessly with self-hosted SOGo server and self-signed certificates. Detects colors and names automagically.
It's totally works w two way sync w zimbra server, thanks a lot, nice app, you should consider to build a beta version soon, thank you.

Work beautifully on my Desire HD. I sync it with my Yahoo Calendar. Looking forward to more features being implemented..such as two-way syncing. Its amazing that there are very few apps that work well with CalDav servers (unless you're using Google calendar), this one fills the gap nicely.
Using this to get my mobileMe calendar on my droid. Works perfectly! Great Work!
Since Google changed their policy with Gmail on handling foreign email addresses, I had to copy each work event manually - this solved it. (my colleagues should follow :-)
So far the only tool that made my android work with Oracle cal server. Good job on alpha!
